OL,3,CThe impact of "news avoidance" on
OL,4,Cbroadcast news
OL,6,FLyse examines the issue of deliberate
OL,7,F"news avoidance" ` a current
OL,8,Fcatchphrase in the industry to refer
OL,9,Fto those people who deliberately try
OL,10,Fto stay away from news.
OL,12,FThis is a worrying trend. It is in
OL,13,Fthis environment that fake news and
OL,14,Fdeliberate disinformation can flourish.
OL,16,FThen, of course, there are those who
OL,17,Fsimply do not engage with the so-
OL,18,Fcalled mainstream media.
OL,20,FIt might also be that they seek
OL,21,F"confirmation bias" ` articles which
OL,22,Freinforce their existing views.
